cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with compressive sampling (CS) in wireless sensor networks (WSNs) for the acquisition of spatially sparse fields. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely category as it deals with the theoretical foundations of CS. The paper also involves system-level considerations such as energy and bandwidth consumption, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. The use of WSNs suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible category. The paper also mentions surveillance applications, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
